Reasoning: The paper discusses a new waveform for reliable communication in high-speed vehicular communication scenarios, which falls under the domain of communication systems (cs.COMM) and networked systems (cs.NI). The paper also discusses the use of practical forward error correction codes, which falls under the domain of information theory (cs.IT). The paper presents results on peak to average power ratio (PAPR), which falls under the domain of multimedia (cs.MM). Finally, the paper discusses the gain obtained by OTFS over OFDM, which falls under the domain of systems and control (cs.SY).
